# Sample HTTP requests for testing the acquireLease endpoint
# Usage: open this file with VS Code and use the REST Client extension, or copy the curl examples.

### Acquire a lease (happy path, with metadata)
POST http://localhost:8080/api/v1/leases
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "owner": "test-user-1",
  "metadata": { "purpose": "integration-test", "requestId": "req-123" }
}

### Acquire a lease from a group
POST http://localhost:8080/api/v1/leases
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "owner": "test-user-1",
  "groupName": "teamcity",
  "metadata": { "purpose": "integration-test", "requestId": "req-123" }
}

### Acquire another lease (happy path, without metadata)
POST http://localhost:8080/api/v1/leases
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "owner": "test-user-2"
}

### Example: conflict response (when no free schemas)
# The server returns 409 with body: { "error": "no free schemas" }
POST http://localhost:8080/api/v1/leases
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "owner": "exhaust-test"
}

### Example: send a heartbeat to keep the lease alive
# send heartbeat for a specific lease (get lease ID from previous acquire response)
POST http://localhost:8080/api/v1/leases/3f910b8b-a7a7-4c88-b5db-97ed1dab0ec3/heartbeat

### Example: release a lease
# release a specific lease (get lease ID from previous acquire response)
POST http://localhost:8080/api/v1/leases/c76c0941-ccdc-467b-a6f8-07f6d2dcf90e/release

### Example: list all schemas
# list all schemas
GET http://localhost:8080/api/v1/status/schemas

### Example: show lease details
# show details of a specific lease (get lease ID from previous acquire response)
GET http://localhost:8080/api/v1/status/lease/d703ef3b-fb10-4711-8899-3bfd86e52615

### Example: show all leases
# list all leases
GET http://localhost:8080/api/v1/status/leases